<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-355-674  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 355 674.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications News  April 1990 v27 n4 p48(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>LAN bridge augurs well; radio is a winner for California databasegiant Oracle.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Relational data base management system vendor Oracle Corp acquiresshort-haul microwave technology to provide a 10M-bit/sec Ethernetlocal area network (LAN) bridge from the firm's Belmont, CA,headquarters to a new 12-story building three miles away.andP;  OracleCommunications Dir Tony Chance selected a Digital Equipment Corp(DEC) Metrowave Bridge which was installed by DEC subcontractorPacific Communications.andP;  The Metrowave Bridge consists of DECEthernet hardware and a M/A-COM Inc (Chelmsford, MA) 23GHzmicrowave radio system.andP;  The DEC hardware includes a DEC LANBridge 100 and a DEC microwave interface which linked to theM/A-COM system, which includes a 2-foot antenna and a MA-23VXradio.andP;  System payback is expected to take just over a year.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Oracle Corp. (communication systems)Digital Equipment Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    ORCL.andO;Product:   Metrowave Bridge (Telecommunications equipment) (installation).andO;Topic:     Microwave CommunicationsSystem DesignSpecificationsCase Study.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>